      </userestrict>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_ead59b61d73b5c14ecce28950c8b2038">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research. The operating notes may contain protected medical information and are closed until processed.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_d09ec32b9cd2dab5baed2ccd73a75756">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Norton Canfield Papers (MS 1293). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_f0ea5fe43313c3a7deed41c8fe0bfbc3">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Norton Canfield: physician; B.S., Dartmouth, 1925; M.D., University of Michigan, 1929; instructor, University of Michigan, 1929; instructor, University of Michigan Hospital, 1930-1933; instructor, Yale Medical School, 1933-1935, assistant professor, 1935-1938, associate professor and Chief of Otolaryngology, 1938-1951, associate clinical professor, 1951-1962; Chief of Otolaryngology and founding director of the Virgin Island Hearing and Speech Center, 1962-1973; private practice,1974-</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_f5bd3cfb9f6504d61246b8f4f6973c62">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Personal papers and research notes of Norton Canfield relating to audiology. Included are papers documenting a national hearing survey, a Connecticut hearing survey, various New Haven, Connecticut projects, and an Army hearing center.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
